{
  "text": "Some results about these are already known. For example, McKay and Wanless [CITATION_1] show that a random Latin square of order n has n (3/2\u2212\u03b5) intercalates, and the probability of a random Latin square of order n not containing any intercalates is O(exp(\u2212n (2\u2212\u03b5) ), for any \u03b5 > 0.",
